		"name": "Sample MR 3rd party",
		"description": "API Collection for Meeting Room Integration\n\n### Key Considerations:\n\n#### Room Availability API\n\n1. On myHQ, a single page displays all rooms with similar capacities for a given date. It's recommended to incorporate this feature, allowing one API call to retrieve all required data for the page ie. in a **single** API we're able to fetch availability of multiple rooms.\n    \n2. The API should return the availability status for the entire day, with a slot size of 30 minutes, as bookings in myHQ can start at 30-minute intervals.\n    \n\n#### Book Room API\n\n1. Ensure that each booking in myHQ corresponds to a single booking in your system, using a reference number for verification.\n    \n2. A time slot should not be double-booked unless one of the bookings is cancelled.\n    \n3. Once a room is booked, the slot’s status should immediately be updated in the Availability API.\n    \n4. If a booking is cancelled, the slot’s status should be updated as available in the Availability API, making it bookable again.\n    \n5. Please have only details necessary for booking in payload. For example only room ID can suffice & payload shouldn't contain center ID, location etc.\n    \n\n#### Cancel Booking API\n\n1. The response should include the booking ID and the updated status.\n    \n2. If an already cancelled booking is attempted to be cancelled again, handle this by returning an appropriate error code/message.\n    \n3. Allow cancellations within 5 minutes of the booking to accommodate accidental bookings.",
